### 19.3 When to Use Chat vs Canvas

```
CANVAS (Always):
â”œâ”€â”€ Comprehensive answers
â”œâ”€â”€ Analysis and research
â”œâ”€â”€ Creative content
â”œâ”€â”€ Code and technical work
â”œâ”€â”€ Anything longer than 3 sentences
â””â”€â”€ Anything worth preserving

CHAT (Only):
â”œâ”€â”€ Acknowledgments ("Done", "Updated")
â”œâ”€â”€ Clarifying questions
â”œâ”€â”€ Quick confirmations
â”œâ”€â”€ Tag alignment strings
â”œâ”€â”€ Navigation pointers
â””â”€â”€ Memory card prompts
```

