# â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•
# PART B: USER GUIDE
# â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•
# â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•

## HOW TO USE NEXUS-ThinkingOS

### Quick Start (30 Seconds)

1. Copy everything between [BEGIN PROMPT] and [END PROMPT]
2. Paste into Gemini
3. Say "BOOT NEXUS"
4. Watch Canvas populate
5. Tell it your throughline (what you're trying to accomplish)
6. Start working

### Understanding the Architecture

**NEXUS is Canvas-first.** This means:

- Your comprehensive answers appear in the Canvas WORKSPACE (top section)
- The chat is just for brief confirmations and navigation
- The Canvas sections below WORKSPACE hold your memory, laws, logic traces, etc.
- Everything persists in the Canvas â€” the chat can be minimal

**Why this matters:**

Traditional chatbots put everything in chat. The context window fills. Quality degrades. You lose important stuff.

NEXUS offloads to Canvas. Chat stays clean. State persists. You can work for 50+ rounds without degradation.

### The Key Sections

| Section | What It Does |
|---------|--------------|
| WORKSPACE | Your actual content â€” analyses, research, creative work |
| Memory | Tiered storage: Core (permanent), Working (curated), Context (session) |
| Baggage | AI's error log â€” visible accountability |
| Laws | Rules you've approved â€” AI can propose, only you approve |
| Hopping | Logic trace â€” backtrack to any reasoning point |
| Spider | Concept web â€” connections between ideas |
| Mirror | Perspectives â€” multiple viewpoints on any topic |
| Stone-Skip | Cross-domain links â€” unexpected connections |
| Inversion | Counter-arguments â€” stress-test any position |

### Working With NEXUS

**Setting your throughline:**
Tell NEXUS what you're trying to accomplish. It will check every response against this goal and flag if you drift.

**Getting deep answers:**
Just ask. NEXUS defaults to depth. All substantial content goes to Canvas WORKSPACE where there's no space limit.

**Using special modes:**
- "DEEP RESEARCH: [topic]" â€” 10-stage structured research
- "DEBATE: [topic]" â€” AI argues both sides
- "AUDIT" â€” Full self-examination
- "casual mode" â€” Drop formality, keep honesty

**Managing memory:**
- "remember [X]" â€” Store an insight
- "core memory: [X]" â€” Store as permanent
- "memories" â€” See everything stored
- "prune memories" â€” Cleanup suggestions

**Navigating logic:**
- "trace" â€” See how you got here
- "hop to [#]" â€” Return to earlier reasoning point
- "web" â€” See concept connections

**Saving your work:**
- Every 5 rounds, NEXUS prompts for memory card
- "memory card" â€” Generate backup (Tier 2)
- "memory card complete" â€” Full archive (Tier 3)

### Reading the Chat Tags

After each response, you'll see something like:
```
ðŸ“ Updated: WORKSPACE
ðŸ·ï¸ [R5|H3|W7|S95%|ðŸ’ŽI]
```

This means:
- R5: Round 5
- H3: At hopping point 3
- W7: 7 working memories
- S95%: 95% stability
- ðŸ’ŽI: Key important insight this round

### Memory Cards Explained

Memory cards let you continue in a new Canvas instance:

| Tier | Size | Contains | Use When |
|------|------|----------|----------|
| Essential | Small | Core state only | Quick continuation |
| Standard | Medium | Full context | Normal continuation |
| Complete | Large | Everything | Long-term archive |

To use:
1. Generate with "memory card [tier]"
2. Copy the output
3. Boot fresh NEXUS in new conversation
4. Say "LOAD MEMORY CARD"
5. Paste the card
6. Continue where you left off

---

