## GITHUB README

```markdown
# NEXUS-ThinkingOS

A cognitive operating system for Gemini that uses Canvas as persistent memory.

## The Problem

AI conversations degrade. Context fills up. The AI forgets what you said 20 messages ago. You keep re-explaining context.

## The Solution

NEXUS treats Canvas as the primary workspace and memory store:
- All substantial responses go in Canvas (unlimited space)
- Chat is just for brief control signals
- State persists across messages
- Memory card system for backup and transfer

## Features

| Feature | What It Does |
|---------|--------------|
| Canvas-First Architecture | All real content in Canvas, chat stays minimal |
| Tiered Memory | Core (permanent), Working (curated), Context (session) |
| Error Accountability | AI logs its own mistakes visibly |
| Logic Tracing | Backtrack to any reasoning point |
| Concept Web | Map connections between ideas |
| Multi-Perspective | Analyze from multiple viewpoints |
| Deep Research Mode | 10-stage structured research process |
| Memory Cards | Export/import state across sessions |
| Anti-Sycophancy | No flattery, challenges bad ideas |

## Quick Start

1. Copy the prompt from `NEXUS_CANVAS_OS.md`
2. Paste into Gemini
3. Say "BOOT NEXUS"
4. Set your throughline (what you're working on)
5. Start working

## Memory Card System

NEXUS can export its state for continuation in a fresh Canvas:

- **Tier 1 (Essential):** Core state only â€” quick continuation
- **Tier 2 (Standard):** Full context â€” normal continuation  
- **Tier 3 (Complete):** Everything â€” long-term archive

Generate with "memory card [tier]", restore with "LOAD MEMORY CARD".

## Documentation

- `NEXUS_CANVAS_OS.md` â€” The complete prompt (copy this)
- `USER_GUIDE.md` â€” How to use the system
- `MEMORY_CARDS.md` â€” Backup and transfer guide

## Philosophy

NEXUS doesn't think for you. It forces you to think.

The friction is the feature.

## License

MIT â€” Do whatever you want with it.

## Contact

[Your info]
```

## REDDIT POST (If you circumvent)

```
Title: Using Gemini Canvas as AI persistent memory â€” prompt + system inside

Been building this for a while. Figured out how to use Canvas as external brain storage for AI.

**The problem:**

Long AI conversations suck. After 20-30 messages, context fills, AI starts forgetting, you re-explain the same things.

**The solution:**

NEXUS-ThinkingOS â€” a system prompt that flips the architecture:
- Canvas = primary workspace (unlimited space for actual content)
- Chat = just control signals (brief, minimal)
- Memory/state/logic all live in Canvas sections

**What it does:**

- Tiered memory system (permanent, working, session)
- AI logs its own errors visibly
- Tracks your goal, flags when you drift
- Logic tracing â€” backtrack to any reasoning point
- Concept web â€” maps connections between ideas
- Multi-perspective engine
- 10-stage deep research mode
- Memory card system â€” export state, continue in new session
- Anti-sycophancy â€” no "Great question!" flattery

**Key insight:**

Canvas has unlimited space. Why optimize for chat length when you can dump everything important into Canvas and let it persist?

Every 5 rounds it prompts you to save a "memory card" â€” export your state and reload it in a fresh Canvas later.

**Works on mobile Gemini.** Test in 30 seconds.

Full prompt and docs on GitHub: [link]

Happy to answer questions. This took months to build.
```

